{"name":"Necklace of Prayer Beads: Six types of magic beads exist. The GM decides the type of each bead on the necklace or determines it randomly. A necklace can have more than one bead of the same type. To use one, you must be wearing the necklace. Each bead contains a spell that you can cast from it as a bonus action (using your spell save DC if a save is necessary). Once a magic bead's spell is cast, that bead can't be used again until the next dawn.","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Necklace of Prayer Beads","keys":["d20","Bead of...","Spell"],"diceKeys":["d20"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>1-6\n\n<b>Bead of...</b>Blessing\n\n<b>Spell</b><strong>Bless</strong>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"tNW6dlzZI8xaztHD"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>7-12\n\n<b>Bead of...</b>Curing\n\n<b>Spell</b><strong>Cure wounds</strong> (2nd level) or <strong></strong><strong>lesser restoration</strong>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,12],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"KmbxwZXCx1fdh6Zr"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>13-16\n\n<b>Bead of...</b>Favor\n\n<b>Spell</b><strong>Greater restoration</strong>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[13,16],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"5vEWv8zvEiZEE23f"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>17-18\n\n<b>Bead of...</b>Smiting\n\n<b>Spell</b><strong>Branding smite</strong>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[17,18],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"eU0eolOB20mPvNNE"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>19\n\n<b>Bead of...</b>Summons\n\n<b>Spell</b><strong>Planar ally</strong>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[19,19],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"e0CQ89DmqXuw2Mpf"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>20\n\n<b>Bead of...</b>Wind walking\n\n<b>Spell</b><strong>Wind walk</strong>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"tYycT2vb6VPwgz75"}],"formula":"d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679699671,"modifiedTime":1677679699671,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"HbyrGqNMyrhpaGYy"}
{"name":"Mizzium Apparatus: 1st-Level Spells","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Mizzium Apparatus","keys":["d6","Spell"],"diceKeys":["d6"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"burning hands","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"441ZgAtvsPWHaWW1"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"chaos bolt (see <a title=\"chapter 2\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ggtr/izzet-league#SpellChaosBolt\">chapter 2</a>)","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"hQgd5S1LXTtBggzS"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"color spray","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"bG5VIPi9xo2JFDou"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"faerie fire","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"PFcdVVI4Didjdx3c"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"fog cloud","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"cuUije5DamOE9jHI"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"thunderwave","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"12KxJ4hZLo4SsYLu"}],"formula":"d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680249542,"modifiedTime":1677680249542,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"HlqGG48QH7Sw2GKv"}
{"name":"Efreeti Bottle: Effect","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Efreeti Bottle","keys":["d100","Effect"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The efreeti attacks you. After fighting for 5 rounds, the efreeti disappears, and the bottle loses its magic.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"qR3pHe1CMy7bi1G6"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The efreeti serves you for 1 hour, doing as you command. Then the efreeti returns to the bottle, and a new stopper contains it. The stopper can't be removed for 24 hours. The next two times the bottle is opened, the same effect occurs. If the bottle is opened a fourth time, the efreeti escapes and disappears, and the bottle loses its magic.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[11,90],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"QGopUF0a7jXngTeV"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The efreeti can cast the wish spell three times for you. It disappears when it grants the final wish or after 1 hour, and the bottle loses its magic.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[91,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"cWEL0mu3qskxNHzU"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679638124,"modifiedTime":1677679638124,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"JG2w5HzqoJMnoy3T"}
{"name":"Manual of Golems: This tome contains information and incantations necessary to make a particular type of golem. To decipher and use the manual, you must be a spellcaster with at least two 5th-level spell slots. A creature that can't use a manual of golems and attempts to read it takes 6d6 psychic damage.","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Manual of Golems","keys":["d20","Golem","Time","Cost"],"diceKeys":["d20"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>1-5\n\n<b>Golem</b>Manual of Clay Golems\n\n<b>Time</b>30 days\n\n<b>Cost</b>65,000 GP","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"EPrHmKZ40YNdAoz7"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>6-17\n\n<b>Golem</b>Manual of Flesh Golems\n\n<b>Time</b>60 days\n\n<b>Cost</b>50,000 GP","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,17],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"qhOq2KQQkL7xHHZO"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>18\n\n<b>Golem</b>Manual of Iron Golems\n\n<b>Time</b>120 days\n\n<b>Cost</b>100,000 GP","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[18,18],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"XxDsHZQWmnSBtSwA"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>19-20\n\n<b>Golem</b>Manual of Stone Golems\n\n<b>Time</b>90 days\n\n<b>Cost</b>80,000 GP","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[19,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Ao4RCpjBfNTUupEP"}],"formula":"d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679876110,"modifiedTime":1677679876110,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"JQpyazxGRM6P4g8U"}
