{"name":"Lantern of Tracking: Lantern of Tracking","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Lantern of Tracking","keys":["d10","Creature Type"],"diceKeys":["d10"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Aberrations","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"SGDwpwjddXpVwBLr"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Celestials","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Lyh7OrnzsXx1V3ZO"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Constructs","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"3NBHExh1jPtkXmvC"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Dragons","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"VM79e1TS0S1pTMxK"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Elementals","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"WJbxWG2zwcp7ExrZ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Fey","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"u6F9MyX6rtoVCzPj"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Fiends","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"fDAWY1whIgpSBefS"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Giants","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"pL1z0E6rRuBFbzPL"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Monstrosities","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"c8B1SAfHkU0NkTEQ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Undead","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"HHcvhU7NnwrOQDUx"}],"formula":"d10","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680311583,"modifiedTime":1677680311583,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Z4vXBMN7i9G04mBw"}
{"name":"Sword of Zariel: Bonds","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Sword of Zariel","keys":["D6","BOND"],"diceKeys":["D6"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I have a favorite religious hymn that I constantly hum.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"6ewEeWN6TRJ7Mnk6"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I must keep a written record of my beliefs and the sins that I witness. When finished, this book will be my gift to the multiverse.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"5OtJmxWjH0JBxXMq"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I have cherished memories of Idyllglen, though I’ve only seen this bucolic town in dreams.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"vxRQRSiHBIEJWBLn"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I would die for those who fight beside me, regardless of their faults.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"hVoPI6N8BsIyi8lz"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I seek to honor the angel Zariel by destroying fiends and other evildoers wherever I find them.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"z5BRkyp7v4brRv0c"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">Sword of Zariel</span> has chosen me. I shall not fail to wield it justly.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"4UCVntO4iXdYJQY3"}],"formula":"","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680294214,"modifiedTime":1677680294214,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"ZOlkL6bjkbUn9REY"}
{"name":"Nathair's Mischief: Mischievous Surge","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Nathair's Mischief","keys":["d4","Effect"],"diceKeys":["d4"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The smell of apple pie fills the air, and each creature in the cube must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become charmed by you until the start of your next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"srtCayLg4rcVr29K"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Bouquets of flowers appear all around, and each creature in the cube must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or be blinded until the start of your next turn as the flowers spray water in their faces.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"imOv4wlP80HaOCmX"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Each creature in the cube must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or begin giggling until the start of your next turn. A giggling creature is incapacitated and uses all its movement to move in a random direction.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"hQN5XkqeSCebWpJq"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Drops of molasses hover in the cube, making it difficult terrain until the start of your next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"PT0n7r5b4NBaUkJO"}],"formula":"d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679530817,"modifiedTime":1677679530817,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"aZ4aCCadD52io29n"}
{"name":"Bag of Beans: Effect","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Bag of Beans","keys":["d100","Effect"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"[[5d4]] ([[/r 5d4]])  toadstoolssprout. If a creature eats a toadstool, roll any die. On an odd roll, the eater must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or take [[/r 5d6[poison] # Poison damage]]  damage and become poisoned for 1 hour. On an even roll, the eater gains[[/r 5d6]]  temporaryhit points for 1 hour.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"pVIzZBpEw64ph1BJ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A geyser erupts and spouts water, beer, berry juice, tea, vinegar, wine, or oil (GM's choice) 30 feet into the air for[[1d12]] ([[/r 1d12]])  rounds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"FhpyoBtDzlU23mVQ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A treant sprouts. There's a 50 percent chance that the treant is chaotic evil and attacks.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[11,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"XU3KMdegJL7U8MKk"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"An animate, immobile stone statue in your likeness rises. It makes verbal threats against you. If you leave it and others come near, it describes you as the most heinous of villains and directs the newcomers to find and attack you. If you are on the same plane of existence as the statue, it knows where you are. The statue becomes inanimate after 24 hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,30],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"3jonrL25Zpbsi3py"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A campfire with blue flames springs forth and burns for 24 hours (or until it is extinguished).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[31,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"sNLUqPvo6HlcEyiw"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"[[1d6 + 6]] ([[/r 1d6 + 6]])  shriekerssprout","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,50],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"NBi2vZd8ApP3n4p8"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"[[1d4 + 8]] ([[/r 1d4 + 8]])  brightpink toads crawl forth. Whenever a toad is touched, it transforms into a Large or smaller monster of the GM's choice. The monster remains for 1 minute, then disappears in a puff of bright pink smoke.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[51,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"B6QvF89VSZECgwc2"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A hungry bulette burrows up and attacks.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,70],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"OYueJ4C8fiZhCgAZ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A fruit tree grows. It has[[1d10 + 20]] ([[/r 1d10 + 20]])  fruit,[[/r 1d8]]  ofwhich act as randomly determined magic potions, while one acts as an ingested poison of the GM's choice. The tree vanishes after 1 hour. Picked fruit remains, retaining any magic for 30 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[71,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"dO4YAq9p9EBrZy5O"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A nest of[[1d4 + 3]] ([[/r 1d4 + 3]])  eggssprings up. Any creature that eats an egg must make a DC 20 Constitution saving throw. On a successful save, a creature permanently increases its lowest ability score by 1, randomly choosing among equally low scores. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/r 10d6[force] # Force damage]]  damage from an internal magical explosion.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,90],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"qwKE3prbUeAGeYJa"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A pyramid with a 60-foot‐square base bursts upward. Inside is a sarcophagus containing a mummy lord. The pyramid is treated as the mummy lord's lair, and its sarcophagus contains treasure of the GM's choice.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[91,99],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"oOEHycMuteb2VwXK"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A giant beanstalk sprouts, growing to a height of the GM's choice. The top leads where the GM chooses, such as to a great view, a cloud giant's castle, or a different plane of existence.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[100,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"1Ab7jbYyAJ0UG8pr"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679571705,"modifiedTime":1677679571705,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"aqxWtrs9dIRBHFen"}
{"name":"Spell Scroll: Scroll Mishap","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Spell Scroll","keys":["d6","Result"],"diceKeys":["d6"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A surge of magical energy deals the caster [[/r 1d6[force] # Force damage]]  damage per level of the spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Ut8OS6xzsDQIl66A"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The spell affects the caster or an ally (determined randomly) instead of the intended target, or it affects a random target nearby if the caster was the intended target.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"xN3v18SBvdjqDfdk"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The spell affects a random location within the spell’s range.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"I7vq8EHZDtpRjQ3g"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The spell’s effect is contrary to its normal one, but neither harmful nor beneficial. For instance, a fireball might produce an area of harmless cold.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"0q2E2jYU52PFlK6A"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster suffers a minor but bizarre effect related to the spell. Such effects last only as long as the original spell’s duration, or[[1d10]] ([[/r 1d10]])  minutesfor spells that take effect instantaneously. For example, a fireball might cause smoke to billow from the caster’s ears for[[/r 1d10]]  minutes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"RcUUqrBmnJmEUoaf"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The spell activates after[[1d12]] ([[/r 1d12]])  hours. If the caster was the intended target, the spell takes effect normally. If the caster was not the intended target, the spell goes off in the general direction of the intended target, up to the spell’s maximum range, if the target has moved away.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"tndxrw9hdzQ1RFZ2"}],"formula":"d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679878024,"modifiedTime":1677679878024,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"cDU1NUwFznAglGUU"}
{"name":"Confusion: Behavior","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Confusion","keys":["d10","Behavior"],"diceKeys":["d10"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The creature uses all its movement to move in a random direction. To determine the direction, roll a[[+ 8]] ([[/r + 8]])  andassign a direction to each die face. The creature doesn't take an action this turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ZdSnFqxd1uFBciVa"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The creature doesn't move or take actions this turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"UatMgyV9DxKV5ng1"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The creature uses its action to make a melee attack against a randomly determined creature within its reach. If there is no creature within its reach, the creature does nothing this turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"QOZGLMgZSfuTLF16"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The creature can act and move normally.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[9,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"8ppsmqJnrAvWafov"}],"formula":"d10","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679530611,"modifiedTime":1677679530611,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"cVGPZMqAathNhK50"}
{"name":"Ring of Resistance: You have resistance to one damage type while wearing this ring. The gem in the ring indicates the type, which the DM chooses or determines randomly.","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Ring of Resistance","keys":["d10","Damage Type","Gem"],"diceKeys":["d10"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>1\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Acid\n\n<b>Gem</b>Pearl","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"oMgB0m5upcUZVZe3"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>2\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Cold\n\n<b>Gem</b>Tourmaline","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"CRmyN355Z7YhDXo4"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>3\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Fire\n\n<b>Gem</b>Garnet","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"xZHHEh2riX8aIF3t"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>4\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Force\n\n<b>Gem</b>Sapphire","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"hg0l2KxFdtqt0qjY"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>5\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Lightning\n\n<b>Gem</b>Citrine","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"gO7Aoufrordc7uo5"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>6\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Necrotic\n\n<b>Gem</b>Jet","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"tchMxBvydcuUfpAN"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>7\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Poison\n\n<b>Gem</b>Amethyst","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"YSM8Qz75kguOGvC8"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>8\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Psychic\n\n<b>Gem</b>Jade","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"cckDBCFIVZ59O3Ed"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>9\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Radiant\n\n<b>Gem</b>Topaz","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"0ZouxwipFQT3DSgQ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 10]] ([[/r + 10]])</b>10\n\n<b>Damage Type</b>Thunder\n\n<b>Gem</b>Spinel","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"NaUlr0jKaKmrpX1A"}],"formula":"d10","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679878037,"modifiedTime":1677679878037,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"dklVwo8Qy0TRdap6"}
{"name":"Scroll of Protection: Creature Type","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Scroll of Protection","keys":["d100","Creature Type"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Aberrations","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"j2HxR00lsgE8PjLV"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Beasts","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[11,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Bsc2HyauoUpToyac"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Celestials","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,30],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Yzo5TqbFd8xxu4fc"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Elementals","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[31,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"N15YWjPaeAgcPrvh"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Fey","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,50],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"RsORiMghDxpKiorK"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Fiends","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[51,75],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"XOt2fmNsZrdq04WT"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Plants","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[76,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ldGyfaIH8EUoiFCM"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Undead","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ydrOONs3TV1CRuSh"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680155137,"modifiedTime":1677680155137,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"gQkW70vWhlA21t7f"}
{"name":"Moonblade: Moonblade Properties","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Moonblade","keys":["d100","Property"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Increase the bonus to attack and damage rolls by 1, to a maximum of +3. Reroll if the <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> already has a +3 bonus.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"IElySQaXo57HKAWk"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> gains a randomly determined minor property (see “<a href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/dmg/treasure#SpecialFeatures\">Special Features</a>”).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"p0KOyWm0kNVPqrAf"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> gains the finesse property.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,82],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"qtJacOe6oHTpKvEs"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> gains the thrown property (range 20/60 feet).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[83,84],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"qV96wEwaKuIj1k60"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> functions as a <span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">defender.</span>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[85,86],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"GOqVf0WBiGjGuq0I"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> scores a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[87,90],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ocQFPeRDuGcrM6PR"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"When you hit with an attack using the <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong>, the attack deals an extra [[/r 1d6[slashing] # Slashing damage]]  damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[91,92],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"l31KqgvjoOS4zHbl"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"When you hit a creature of a specific type (such as dragon, fiend, or undead) with the <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong>, the target takes an extra[[1d6]] ([[/r 1d6]])  damageof one of these types: acid, cold, fire, lightning, or thunder.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[93,94],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"fB6tUek7CmeLi9tB"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You can use a bonus action to cause the <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> to flash brightly. Each creature that can see you and is within 30 feet of you must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become blinded for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. This property can’t be used again until you take a short rest while attuned to the weapon.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[95,96],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"OubIv5cmfy6YodLs"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> functions as a <span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">ring of spell storing</span>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[97,98],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"uDGyfHZGmR1SuWjE"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You can use an action to call forth an elfshadow, provided that you don’t already have one serving you<span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">.</span> The elfshadow appears in an unoccupied space within 120 feet of you. It uses the statistics for a <span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Bold-Sans-Serif\">shadow</span>, except it is neutral, immune to effects that turn undead, and doesn’t create new shadows. You control this creature, deciding how it acts and moves. It remains until it drops to 0 hit points or you dismiss it as an action.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[99,99],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Vix5ihmJehvJjV7f"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The <strong><span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">moonblade</span></strong> functions as a <span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">vorpal sword</span>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[100,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"S07jkXMNjCEhxEUn"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680173093,"modifiedTime":1677680173093,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"mNIcZCFuWuwnNiL5"}
{"name":"Bag of Tricks: Tan Bag of Tricks","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Bag of Tricks","keys":["d8","Creature"],"diceKeys":["d8"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Jackal","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"LlqUAnK27wrTxjwj"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Ape","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"knADs7X3VRNerPdt"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Baboon","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"fAzbh34XGWR9QoAz"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Axe beak","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"bIG3SILIja4GxHT1"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Black bear","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"1IndbB3dPa49iw6f"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Giant weasel","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"3kKj72L9dZYU0Smm"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Giant hyena","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"lXzTxRpJuuBtMWRZ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Tiger","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"0i8cpc3VzH9eyomT"}],"formula":"d8","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679577645,"modifiedTime":1677679577645,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"rKEDKD57HFttsceA"}
{"name":"Wand of Wonder: Effect","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Wand of Wonder","keys":["d100","Effect"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>slow</strong>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"2XrGikc4EamGKchW"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>faerie fire</strong>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"cxNppsuVvAioOqjB"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You are stunned until the start of your next turn, believing something awesome just happened.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[11,15],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"DCAS18lvVAYpaJcz"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>gust of wind</strong>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[16,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"OUdat5zDUoWc5WVY"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>detect thoughts</strong> on the target you chose. If you didn't target a creature, you instead take [[/r 1d6[psychic] # Psychic damage]]  damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,25],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"CaZftxYTM9PJVnCc"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>stinking cloud</strong>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[26,30],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"B20SKCu0g5d2sChN"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Heavy rain falls in a 60-foot radius centered on the target. The area becomes lightly obscured. The rain falls until the start of your next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[31,33],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"vYlGS3uiWE4CCOgC"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"An animal appears in the unoccupied space nearest the target. The animal isn't under your control and acts as it normally would. Roll a[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])  todetermine which animal appears. On a 01-25, a rhinoceros appears; on a 26-50, an elephant appears; and on a 51-100, a rat appears.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[34,36],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"o0ABgz54NMzymZLl"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>lightning bolt</strong>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[37,46],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"CGN8YdmFmhAmNzb4"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A cloud of 600 oversized butterflies fills a 30‐foot radius centered on the target. The area becomes heavily obscured. The butterflies remain for 10 minutes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[47,49],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"PxVx1Y0Hwgq6b7yX"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You enlarge the target as if you had cast <strong></strong><strong>enlarge/reduce</strong>. If the target can't be affected by that spell, or if you didn't target a creature, you become the target.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[50,53],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"GWjb24En7IFHBauO"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>darkness</strong>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[54,58],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"2A0G8I4k7rgued8j"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Grass grows on the ground in a 60‐foot radius centered on the target. If grass is already there, it grows to ten times its normal size and remains overgrown for 1 minute.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[59,62],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"sSuChwH9jvmuVkmI"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"An object of the GM's choice disappears into the Ethereal Plane. The object must be neither worn nor carried, within 120 feet of the target, and no larger than 10 feet in any dimension.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[63,65],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"QY2V8W6zCiHxFI8x"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You shrink yourself as if you had cast <strong></strong><strong>enlarge/reduce</strong> on yourself.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[66,69],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ltftIshB87nSVoxC"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>fireball</strong>.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[70,79],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"XqFw5sZhZqsOnrky"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"You cast <strong></strong><strong>invisibility</strong> on yourself.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[80,84],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"g0G2zlvE4H24gchW"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Leaves grow from the target. If you chose a point in space as the target, leaves sprout from the creature nearest to that point. Unless they are picked off, the leaves turn brown and fall off after 24 hours.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[85,87],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Znykk9Mo2RV6kjjN"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A stream of[[1d4]] ([[/r 1d4]])× 10 gems, each worth 1 gp, shoots from the wand's tip in a line 30 feet long and 5 feet wide. Each gem deals 1 bludgeoning damage, and the total damage of the gems is divided equally among all creatures in the line.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[88,90],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"8i8hdVpvalky92y8"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A burst of colorful shimmering light extends from you in a 30‐foot radius. You and each creature in the area that can see must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become blinded for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[91,95],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"syqkrKBJzAcaFf6T"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The target's skin turns bright blue for[[1d10]] ([[/r 1d10]])  days. If you chose a point in space, the creature nearest to that point is affected.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[96,97],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"3H3ElEWh6Lt2N9iz"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"If you targeted a creature, it must make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw. If you didn't target a creature, you become the target and must make the saving throw. If the saving throw fails by 5 or more, the target is instantly petrified. On any other failed save, the target is restrained and begins to turn to stone. While restrained in this way, the target must repeat the saving throw at the end of its next turn, becoming petrified on a failure or ending the effect on a success. The petrification lasts until the target is freed by the <strong></strong><strong>greater restoration</strong> spell or similar magic.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[98,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"z8id1YZxbyk5OpaZ"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677679828600,"modifiedTime":1677679828600,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"rhqIl8uCtjgKuXYH"}
{"name":"Whisper Jar: RECORDING","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Whisper Jar","keys":["D8","RECORDING"],"diceKeys":["D8"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A live recording of the only performance of the mostly forgotten stage play <span class=\"Sans-Serif-Character-Styles_Italic-Sans-Serif\">Tabaxi on a Hot Tin Roof</span>","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"FOQtXHnULoKir69A"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The life’s work of the loremonger who owned the jar before you","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"7HnuNX5wO7F2Ipu6"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Every courageous thought you’ve ever had, to cover for how scared you are most of the time","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"FdeFyUybM1rMQnwm"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Everything, because everyone else around you will eat their words one day!","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"QEtNPu1gFZUG3nIm"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The top seven places to eat fried rat skewers in every settlement you’ve ever visited","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"xP0hRL8lPsRdPIJA"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The entire family tree of every royal line, extant or lost, in Faerûn","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"efopqi1OWbLzMr4G"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A moment-by-moment review of your favorite Jim Darkmagic stage performance","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"eqcAEPmQEkcWnQDO"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The sound of raucous applause, which you play back liberally","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"DA52kiRC21TYh1xH"}],"formula":"","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680281177,"modifiedTime":1677680281177,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"vfaDENikvQ17Ox7u"}
{"name":"Sword of Zariel: Personality Traits","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Sword of Zariel","keys":["D8","PERSONALITY TRAIT"],"diceKeys":["D8"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I treat all beings, even enemies, with respect.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"GsKpdHE8feNYWnct"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I won’t tell a lie.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"50uGPj91G5W20GDg"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I enjoy sharing my philosophical worldview and experiences with others.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Mffb98OM8UPev5NV"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I cut right to the chase in every conversation.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"tOKK4bp87moLCGau"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I often quote (or misquote) religious texts.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"uMbpWxxI1Kz0Fr2m"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I anger quickly when I witness cruelty or injustice.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"DVrOjaGYoYfiQW2l"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"My praise and trust are earned and never given freely.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"JpE8MrWxXPEiMCZR"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"I like everything clean and organized.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"5JrVZspS9Aoh9mix"}],"formula":"","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680294207,"modifiedTime":1677680294207,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"vpAPRy2oghhmYLE5"}
{"name":"Hook of Fisher's Delight: Hook of Fisher’s Delight","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Hook of Fisher's Delight","keys":["d20","Fish Color","Result"],"diceKeys":["d20"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>1-10\n\n<b>Fish Color</b>Green with copper bands\n\n<b>Result</b>This tasty fish provides a day’s worth of nourishment to one creature that eats it. The fish loses this property and rots if it’s not eaten within 24 hours of being caught.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"8yCpJKKrYsgvcrke"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>11-14\n\n<b>Fish Color</b>Yellow with black stripes\n\n<b>Result</b>Once removed from the hook, this awful-tasting fish can be thrown up to 120 feet, targeting a creature the thrower can see. The target must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. The fish then disappears.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[11,14],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"I1ZISzh94iLobMHx"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>15-18\n\n<b>Fish Color</b>Blue with white bands\n\n<b>Result</b>When released from the hook, this fish squirms free, sprouts wings, follows you around, and sings a beautiful tune in Aquan. It disappears after[[/r 2d4]]  hoursor when reduced to 0 hit points. The fish uses the quipper stat block, except that it can breathe air and has a flying speed of 30 feet.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[15,18],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"FotDBHIjrD0tZXqv"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 20]] ([[/r + 20]])</b>19-20\n\n<b>Fish Color</b>Gold with silver stripes\n\n<b>Result</b>This tasty fish provides a day’s worth of nourishment to one creature that eats it and grants[[/r 2d10]]  temporaryhit points to that creature. The fish loses these properties and rots if it’s not eaten within 24 hours of being caught.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[19,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"hcrZJLgHuTPW5qi0"}],"formula":"d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680311581,"modifiedTime":1677680311581,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"vtQSEexypNKe09FP"}
{"name":"Crook of Rao: Extraplanar Reversal","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Crook of Rao","keys":["d100","Effect"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A portal to a random plane opens. The portal closes after 5 minutes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,25],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"1IeaTiluiLv7ueRL"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"[[2d4]] ([[/r 2d4]])  impsand[[/r 2d4]]  quasitsappear.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[26,45],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"RarEGcVSvK5sOvjA"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"[[1d8]] ([[/r 1d8]])  succubi/incubi appear.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[46,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"bat7dYTxnKizpuu9"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"[[1d10]] ([[/r 1d10]])  barbeddevils and[[/r 1d10]]  vrocksappear.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,70],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ETBdGzmewUKYojlF"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"1 arcanaloth, 1 night hag, and 1 rakshasa appear.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[71,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"lfHniodNJSlX1gFC"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"1 ice devil and 1 marilith appear.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,85],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"lZtsaOuQdu3rRNL5"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"1 balor and 1 pit fiend appear. At the DM’s discretion, a portal opens into the presence of an archdevil or demon lord instead, then closes after 5 minutes.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[86,90],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"U4zEs2AMlXtmo3oK"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Iggwilv’s Curse (see the Iggwilv’s Curse property).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[91,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"NQ7PkGgVYwiE1t4R"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680331165,"modifiedTime":1677680331165,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"6BKWA7iCjFumd51u"}
{"name":"Luba's Tarokka of Souls: Prisoners of Fate. Whenever you use the Twist of Fate property, there is a chance that one of the souls trapped in the deck escapes. Roll d100 and consult the Souls of the Tarokka table. If you roll one of the high cards, the soul associated with it escapes. You can find its statistics in the Monster Manual. If you roll a soul that has already escaped, roll again.","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Luba's Tarokka of Souls","keys":["d100","Card","Soul"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>1</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Artifact\n\n<b>Soul</b>Flameskull","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"vn8Lc9XtyBuXzIQy"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>2</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Beast\n\n<b>Soul</b>Wraith","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"k2C5Sect2xj1Zi1H"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>3</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Broken One\n\n<b>Soul</b>Banshee","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ifFuhGeSpTgFEg1p"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>4</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Darklord\n\n<b>Soul</b>Vampire","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"je6R9lyLmEMeH6cb"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>5</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Donjon\n\n<b>Soul</b>Mummy","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"nK0ChaJCdm3u2kfF"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>6</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Executioner\n\n<b>Soul</b>Death knight","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Hstg68INgdBOtlR8"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>7</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Ghost\n\n<b>Soul</b>Ghost","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"eJx51jS6SQ8ExIcF"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>8</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Horseman\n\n<b>Soul</b>Mummy lord","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Pu2YTZG9flLAqn4k"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>9</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Innocent\n\n<b>Soul</b>Ghost","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"NSE8HytGTor04dKO"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>10</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Marionette\n\n<b>Soul</b>Mummy","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"CTd94XQw2HmuAFjn"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>11</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Mists\n\n<b>Soul</b>Wraith","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"WWNEPI7RD824UHnR"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>12</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Raven\n\n<b>Soul</b>Vampire spawn","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"PzE8RgqllzGkNNYd"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>13</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Seer\n\n<b>Soul</b>Vampire","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[13,13],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"8Tp2pFAcL14dakGg"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>14</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>Tempter\n\n<b>Soul</b>Vampire spawn","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[14,14],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"avpU2QDS6RFhixKd"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[+ 100]] ([[/r + 100]])</b><strong>15-00</strong>\n\n<b>Card</b>—\n\n<b>Soul</b>—","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[15,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"X38oLpLZwlWgGr9A"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680332882,"modifiedTime":1677680332882,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"QbkdQ7XFsiQNj7kN"}
{"name":"Outer Essence Shard: Outer Essence Shards","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Outer Essence Shard","keys":["d4","Property"],"diceKeys":["d4"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Lawful. You can end one of the following conditions affecting yourself or one creature you can see within 30 feet of you: charmed, blinded, deafened, frightened, poisoned, or stunned.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"RIk5kW3vQF6bDsLR"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Chaotic. Choose one creature who takes damage from the spell. That target has disadvantage on attack rolls and ability checks made before the start of your next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"0LCaWnTSAm5F10ia"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Good. You or one creature of your choice that you can see within 30 feet of you gains[[3d6]] ([[/r 3d6]])  temporaryhit points.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"fJuMUOgHEsSZuAV2"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Evil. Choose one creature who takes damage from the spell. That target takes an extra [[/r 3d6[necrotic] # Necrotic damage]]  damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"BzNztVHLfR2OIkN8"}],"formula":"d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680337883,"modifiedTime":1677680337883,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"nPklIm5UHd95oKSg"}
{"name":"Elemental Essence Shard: Elemental Essence Shards","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Elemental Essence Shard","keys":["d4","Property"],"diceKeys":["d4"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Air.</strong> You can immediately fly up to 60 feet without provoking opportunity attacks.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"xS57ljcgCjTcm1Wa"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Earth.</strong> You gain resistance to a damage type of your choice until the start of your next turn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"5NylgeCLCmQJUCBA"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Fire.</strong> One target of the spell that you can see catches fire. The burning target takes [[/r 2d10[fire] # Fire damage]]  damage at the start of its next turn, and then the flames go out.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ysIDAXeVGQ5ms3ZR"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<strong>Water.</strong> You create a wave of water that bursts out from you in a 10-foot radius. Each creature of your choice that you can see in that area takes [[/r 2d6[cold] # Cold damage]]  damage and must succeed on a Strength saving throw against your spell save DC or be pushed 10 feet away from you and fall prone.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"9Ic11vza5SrRRvG6"}],"formula":"d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680342786,"modifiedTime":1677680342786,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"CxfiV3XkqBgL3DmU"}
{"name":"Teeth of Dahlver-Nar: Teeth of Dahlver-Nar","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Teeth of Dahlver-Nar","keys":["1d20","Tale and Tooth","Creatures Summoned","Implanted Effect"],"diceKeys":["1d20"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>1\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Staring Cats of Uldun-dar (ivory cat molar)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>9 cats\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>The tooth has 8 charges. As an action, you can expend 1 charge to cast the revivify spell from the tooth. If you are dead at the start of your turn, the tooth expends 1 charge and casts revivify on you.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"4uV3fdS1ZxzEgR92"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>2\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Duggle’s Surprising Day (human molar)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 commoner\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>When you finish a long rest, the tooth casts sanctuary (DC 18) on you, and the spell lasts for 24 hours or until you break it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"MBwEXOIns4T9LxP8"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>3\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Golden Age of Dhakaan (golden goblin bicuspid)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>10 goblins, 1 goblin boss\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>When you are hit by an attack and an ally is within 5 feet of you, you can use your reaction to cause them to be hit instead. You can’t use this reaction again until you finish a short or long rest.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"W9MgZ39AAFH02dg4"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>4\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Mill Road Murders (halfling canine)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>3 green hags in a coven\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>When you damage a target that hasn’t taken a turn in this combat, the target takes an extra [[/r 3d10[slashing] # Slashing damage]]  damage from ghostly blades.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"NGocvPbS6BB8EZeD"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>5\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Dooms of the Malpheggi (emerald lizardfolk fang)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 lizardfolk queen and 4 lizardfolk\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You gain reptilian scales, granting you a +2 bonus to your AC. Additionally, when you finish a long rest, you must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or gain 1 level of exhaustion.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"dQ2ro05ppfD3zaSm"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>6\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Stable Hand’s Secret (sweet-tasting human canine)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>2 incubi\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>When you make a Charisma check against a humanoid, you can roll a[[/r + 10]]  andadd the number rolled as a bonus to the result. The creature then becomes hostile to you at the next dawn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"fD37gtndbsT7lxE3"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>7\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Donkey’s Dream (rainbow-colored donkey molar)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 unicorn\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>The tooth has 3 charges. As an action, you can expend 1 charge to touch a creature. The target regains [[/r 2d8 + 2]]  hit points, and all diseases and poisons affecting it are removed. When you use this action, a shimmering image of a unicorn’s horn appears until the end of your turn, sprouting from your forehead. The tooth regains all expended charges daily at dawn. You gain the following flaw: “When I see wickedness in action, I must oppose it.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"aiss0Y7KAAA4Cntg"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>8\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Beyond the Rock of Bral (silver mind flayer tooth)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>2 mind flayers\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You gain <a href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/mm/introduction#Telepathy\">telepathy</a> out to 120 feet as described in the <em><a href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/mm\">Monster Manual</a></em>, and you can cast the detect thoughts spell at will, requiring no components. You also have disadvantage on Wisdom (Insight) and Wisdom (Perception) checks from constant whispers of memories and nearby minds.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"WGim9QYH8GluQTaV"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>9\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Disappearances of Half Hollow (vomerine tooth of a Large toad)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>4 giant toads\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>Your long jump is up to 30 feet and your high jump is up to 15 feet, with or without a running start.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"9CKeYBqV8Tnb1fko"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>10\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Legendry of Phantoms and Ghosts (obsidian human molar)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 giant octopus, 1 mage, 1 specter\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>As an action, you can use the tooth to cast the Evard’s black tentacles spell (DC 18). Once this property is used, it can’t be used again until the next dawn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"gAooofNHqMhYx7uC"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>11\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Thousand Deaths of Jander Sunstar (yellowed vampire fang)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 vampire\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You can make a bite attack as an unarmed strike. On a hit, it deals [[/r 1d6[piercing] # Piercing damage]]  damage plus [[/r 3d6[necrotic] # Necrotic damage]]  damage. You regain a number of hit points equal to the necrotic damage dealt. While you are in sunlight, you can’t regain hit points.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"qt6Czh9jfFVromCc"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>12\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Nightmares of Kaggash (twisted beholder tooth)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 beholder\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>As an action, you can cast the eyebite spell from the tooth. Once you use this action, it can’t be used again until the next dawn. Whenever you finish a long rest, roll a[[/r + 20]]. Ona 20, an aberration chosen by the DM appears within 30 feet of you and attacks.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"wvUMGIKjsH5JYmqj"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>13\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Three Bridges to the Sky (lapis lazuli oni fang)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>3 oni\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You gain a flying speed of 30 feet, and you can use the tooth to cast the detect magic spell at will. While you are attuned to fewer than 3 magic items, you gain 1 level of exhaustion that can’t be removed until you are attuned to three or more magic items.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[13,13],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"k6Jkp9NEdxxFroGg"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>14\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Claws of Dragotha (broken translucent fang)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 adult red dracolich\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You can use the tooth to cast the create undead spell. Once this property is used, it can’t be used again until the next dawn. Each time you create an undead creature using the tooth, a skeleton, zombie, or ghoul also appears at a random location within 5 miles of you, searching for the living to kill. A humanoid killed by these undead rises as the same type of undead at the next midnight.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[14,14],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"6mNS2xHtRykSJiDI"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>15\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Ashes of the Ages and Eternal Fire (jade humanoid bicuspid)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 dao, 1 djinni, 1 efreeti, 1 marid\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You can use the tooth to cast counterspell at 9th level. Once you use this property, it can’t be used again until the next dawn. Whenever you finish a long rest, if you haven’t used the tooth to counter a spell since your last long rest, your hit point maximum is reduced by[[/r 2d10]]. Ifthis reduces your hit point maximum to 0, you die.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[15,15],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ZjYFj7HHxX5DMmak"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>16\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Daughters of Bel (green steel pit fiend fang)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 pit fiend\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You can use the tooth to cast dominate monster (DC 18). Once you use this property, it can’t be used again until the next dawn. You smell strongly of burning sulfur.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[16,16],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"LRKVybOAQPSPGsSP"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>17\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Why the Sky Screams (blue dragon fang)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 ancient blue dragon\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You gain immunity to lightning damage and vulnerability to thunder damage.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[17,17],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"yPCaWibf6Gpf7YUI"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>18\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>The Last Tarrasque (jagged sliver of tarrasque tooth)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 tarrasque (ignores you and your commands; appears for[[/r 1d4]]  roundsthen vanishes)\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You deal double damage to objects and structures. If you take 20 or more damage in one turn, you must succeed on a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw or spend your next turn in a murderous fury. During this rage, you must use your action to make an unarmed strike against a creature that damaged you, or a random creature you can see if you weren’t damaged by a creature, moving as close as you can to the target if necessary.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[18,18],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"eRsxuv7dobRjwLq2"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>19\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Incendax’s Tooth (ruby-veined red dragon fang)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 ancient red dragon\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>You gain immunity to fire damage, and as an action, you can exhale fire in a 90-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 24 Dexterity saving throw, taking [[/r 26d6[fire] # Fire damage]]  damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. After using the breath weapon, you gain 2 levels of exhaustion.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[19,19],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"p4K3DlsXoCBvJGNC"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>[[1d20]] ([[/r 1d20]])</b>20\n\n<b>Tale and Tooth</b>Dahlver-Nar’s Tooth (dusty human molar)\n\n<b>Creatures Summoned</b>1 priest\n\n<b>Implanted Effect</b>As an action you can call on a divine force to come to your aid. Describe the assistance you seek, and the DM decides the nature of the intervention; the effect of any cleric spell would be appropriate. Once this property is used, it can’t be used again for 7 days.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"AO0XedA2pBtQIdmR"}],"formula":"1d20","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677680344727,"modifiedTime":1677680344727,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"iCp9gHujH6ggIRiR"}
{"name":"Baphomet: Madness of Baphomet","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Baphomet","keys":["d100","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“My anger consumes me. I can’t be reasoned with when my rage has been stoked.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"MAoUXrz4mGhmttn7"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I degenerate into beastly behavior, seeming more like a wild animal than a thinking being.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"eIt9qMGJNrQxKHHE"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“The world is my hunting ground. Others are my prey.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"eVnCUzDyhrVUYijV"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Hate comes easily to me and explodes into rage.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"pVmPtkCKZpXx4qt3"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I see those who oppose me not as people, but as beasts meant to be preyed upon.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"AhLR5U20stBjcQYZ"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682045869,"modifiedTime":1677682045869,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"DmD4WdhOVrlO7Sz1"}
{"name":"Belashyrra: Madness of Belashyrra","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Belashyrra","keys":["d6","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d6"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I constantly see shapes moving in the shadows.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"LdS6xcnOOgujZKCK"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I perceive certain types of people — vocations or entire societies — as hideous monsters.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"UCYgUkurYM9Xb7DY"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Someone is watching everything I do.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"wBp2p9SoptzWKDK8"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“When I close my eyes, I see my past misdeeds.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"zYbBXiZqICOauL8N"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I don’t trust my sight. I have no idea what’s real and what’s a hallucination.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Ab9BKz1nTnfRH0u1"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Something watches the world through my eyes. To thwart them, I keep my eyes closed or covered.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"QRJWUnoXyTKwxCSK"}],"formula":"d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682046715,"modifiedTime":1677682046715,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"haNWWFD8Mp494DMD"}
{"name":"Demogorgon: Madness of Demogorgon","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Demogorgon","keys":["d100","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Someone is plotting to kill me. I need to strike first to stop them!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"iCbfIvlABHTcp2sO"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“There is only one solution to my problems: kill them all!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"blhgBQcs1VpXtMxm"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“There is more than one mind inside my head.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"HIw00An09IYaguR0"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“If you don’t agree with me, I’ll beat you into submission to get my way.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"McPTEjcc7hf3gsRo"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I can’t allow anyone to touch anything that belongs to me. They might try to take it away from me!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"OruKG55zT226qREo"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682053110,"modifiedTime":1677682053110,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"k8kUaPglAqBF76rU"}
{"name":"Dyrrn: Madness of Dyrrn","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Dyrrn","keys":["d6","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d6"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“There’s an illithid parasite living in my brain!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"06XswJZcf4THiNWI"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I can feel myself evolving into an aberration.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"alfy2QBa2hbVAId6"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Aberrations are the only natural things.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"hdXZVEio6iwAnuus"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“A part of me has become a conscious entity.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"NcRluBnOtERsSArr"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“My opponents must bow down to a mind flayer!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"pts7fm6YzwMRbe6Z"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Dyrrn and the mind flayers simply want to unite all sentient creatures in collective consciousness. And I receive messages from the group mind!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"bm7Lg0cjNxjOOkEW"}],"formula":"d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682057372,"modifiedTime":1677682057372,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"qurg5lppmsaHpC0Q"}
{"name":"Fraz-Urb’luu: Madness of Fraz-Urb’luu","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Fraz-Urb’luu","keys":["d100","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I never let anyone know the truth about my actions or intentions, even if doing so would be beneficial to me.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"V0VszwHCADTr7z2I"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I have intermittent hallucinations and fits of catatonia.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"nxPjiwS6mYOKHf6w"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“My mind wanders as I have elaborate fantasies that have no bearing on reality. When I return my focus to the world, I have a hard time remembering that it was just a daydream.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"Riec39KATnBmQgVB"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I convince myself that things are true, even in the face of overwhelming evidence to the contrary.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"zc6tXwCOiAIaEoJH"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“My perception of reality doesn’t match anyone else’s. It makes me prone to violent delusions that make no sense to anyone else.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"BJ7WT4lNxHG05lbN"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682060113,"modifiedTime":1677682060113,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"4te7i2UR6zMQvNx5"}
{"name":"Graz’zt: Madness of Graz’zt","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Graz’zt","keys":[" d100 ","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":[" d100 "]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“There is nothing in the world more important than me and my desires.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"msiptQ05aFrbixE0"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Anyone who doesn’t do exactly what I say doesn’t deserve to live.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"fqWCDMV7MzBnEfvf"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Mine is the path of redemption. Anyone who says otherwise is intentionally misleading you.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"HecnNPsrKA3gV1gj"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I will not rest until I have made someone else mine, and doing so is more important to me than my own life—or the lives of others.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"JbPsJANdMxB2oHdD"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“My own pleasure is of paramount importance. Everything else, including social graces, is a triviality.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,90],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"ILBfuTGgu3muIB6s"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“Anything that can bring me happiness should be enjoyed immediately. There is no point to saving anything pleasurable for later.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[91,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"cvlquVS5rdZ4W0IQ"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682064662,"modifiedTime":1677682064662,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"s2ml7Zrzh2lw40O2"}
{"name":"Juiblex: Madness of Juiblex","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Juiblex","keys":["d100","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I must consume everything I can!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"XRrJdgsOSHXkUCqH"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I refuse to part with any of my possessions.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"YQEUqXxHBYefBSn9"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I’ll do everything I can to get others to eat and drink beyond their normal limits.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"wYpAkZYAstQiR6vb"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I must possess as many material goods as I can.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"8cPZIaYA8poUN3ph"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“My personality is irrelevant. I am defined by what I consume.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"KiXWmDtdwXkbuwKm"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682069638,"modifiedTime":1677682069638,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"p0FtWJr1yBIiY3lw"}
{"name":"Orcus: Madness of Orcus","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Orcus","keys":["d100","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I often become withdrawn and moody, dwelling on the insufferable state of life.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"CMAJigzQZD6k5uHa"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I am compelled to make the weak suffer.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"L26L7qFyP9n0jKNW"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I have no compunction against tampering with the dead in my search to better understand death.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"9gA8nvWRBym1qnno"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I want to achieve the everlasting existence of undeath.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"91bODdaltgzI9vCO"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I am awash in the awareness of life’s futility.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"MJzSq511IhHwp2Fp"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682083242,"modifiedTime":1677682083242,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"jtnthup0q3CCLcsf"}
{"name":"Yeenoghu: Madness of Yeenoghu","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Yeenoghu","keys":["d100","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I get caught up in the flow of anger, and try to stoke others around me into forming an angry mob.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"pb5ar2jtmocGoWBC"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“The flesh of other intelligent creatures is delicious!”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"mNojEPViTbc2E9Ne"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I rail against the laws and customs of civilization, attempting to return to a more primitive time.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"zCvaqnIfLSGzr9Av"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I hunger for the deaths of others, and am constantly starting fights in the hope of seeing bloodshed.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"mjn3Ucp6bUlNXf3T"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I keep trophies from the bodies I have slain, turning them into adornments.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"A3CgjGzvu2e60qvU"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682102762,"modifiedTime":1677682102762,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"D6bbHvaVSkLyopHK"}
{"name":"Zuggtmoy: Madness of Zuggtmoy","flags":{"ddbimporter":{"parentName":"Zuggtmoy","keys":["d100","Flaw (lasts until cured)"],"diceKeys":["d100"]}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I see visions in the world around me that others do not.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[1,20],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"0oE7PyQPhYbt2TjY"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I periodically slip into a catatonic state, staring off into the distance for long stretches at a time.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[21,40],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"BjElWFhSJr9yQOqH"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I see an altered version of reality, with my mind convincing itself that things are true even in the face of overwhelming evidence to the contrary.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[41,60],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"cKHItrLulFkcWB9v"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“My mind is slipping away, and my intelligence seems to wax and wane.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[61,80],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"E8xwtOIdO2ubKzaQ"},{"flags":{},"type":0,"text":"“I am constantly scratching at unseen fungal infections.”","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","weight":1,"range":[81,100],"drawn":false,"documentCollection":"","documentId":null,"_id":"fcyUNu8x71Q6CZNW"}],"formula":"d100","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true,"ownership":{"default":0,"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.5","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1677682105424,"modifiedTime":1677682105424,"lastModifiedBy":"7zB0QH211uvK7gvA"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Vn80ZbhlzZQ94esE"}
